20/03/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Officials say the armed forces and intelligence services, as well as other relevant authorities, were placed on a higher state of alert Wednesday (19 March), in response to the launch of the US-led military strike against Iraq. 
Law enforcement personnel joined border patrols at the northeast border to prevent a possible wave of refugees. 
Security at foreign diplomatic missions in the country has also been increased. 
The Civil Aviation Service adds that it is fully prepared to secure the safety of airports and air transportation. 
(MPA - 20/03/03; ANA - 19/03/03)
